---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import NetworkGraph from "../components/NetworkGraph.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Networks — Agents of Chaos"
  description="A map of the multi-agent landscape: who is building and deploying AI agents, how they relate, and where independent red-teaming is needed most."
>
  <div class="reading">
    <div class="page-head">
      <h1>Networks</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">The landscape of who is deploying agents — and where the harms will land.</p>
    </div>

    <p>
      Multi-agent systems are spreading across labs, startups, and regulated
      enterprises faster than anyone is stress-testing them. This is our working
      map of that landscape: each dot is a company building or deploying agents.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Color</strong> marks the vertical — frontier labs, agent-native
      startups, banks and fintech, healthcare, security vendors, and the rest.
      <strong>Size</strong> tracks how much each one runs agents in production,
      which is also how much it needs red-teaming. <strong>Lines</strong> are
      real ties: who builds on whom, who shares an investor, who competes. Solid
      lines are verified; dashed are inferred. Click any company for the detail.
    </p>

    <span class="section-label"><span class="num">01</span>/ landscape</span>
  </div>

  <NetworkGraph />

  <div class="reading">
    <p class="subtitle" style="margin-top:1.1rem">
      Drag to explore, scroll to zoom, double-click to reframe. The map is a
      work in progress — corrections welcome at
      <a href="/contact">contact</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
